{"key": "introPrepareSpace", "rev": 1, "text": " This audio offers some practical recommendations for your meditation space. We encourage you to meditate anywhere under any conditions. However, if you have a choice, we could recommend that you use a quiet place with as few distractions as possible. If you can, use soft or dimmed lighting to create a gentle atmosphere so that your visual processing is not being overly stimulated. These are simply recommendations. We understand that ideal conditions are not always possible. Therefore, practice what you have. The most important thing is to meditate. Regarding the meditating position, we recommend a straight and upright posture that ensures that you remain in wakeful attention. Avoid drowsiness or over relaxation. Please make sure that you avoid slouching and that you maintain an upright vertical posture. Wakefulness during meditation is essential. If sitting on the floor is uncomfortable, you may use a chair. If you can, avoid leaning against the backrest. Allow the shoulders to soften and let the arms and hands remain free of tension. You may close your eyes during meditation. However, if closing the eyes feels either difficult or increases restlessness, keep them slightly open. In this case, you may let your gaze rest downward at a 45 degree angle, peacefully without focusing. Aim to remain motionless.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 4.9399999999999995, "end": 11.6, "text": " This audio offers some practical recommendations for your meditation space.", "tokens": [50364, 639, 6278, 7736, 512, 8496, 10434, 337, 428, 12537, 1901, 13, 51104], "temperature": 0, "avg_logprob": -0.2542098539846915, "compression_ratio": 1.2980769230769231, "no_speech_prob": 0.1336078643798828, "words": [{"word": " This", "start": 4.9399999999999995, "end": 5.98, "probability": 0.8877778649330139}, {"word": " audio", "start": 5.98, "end": 6.26, "probability": 0.9170306921005249}, {"word": " offers", "start": 6.26, "end": 6.78, "p